getOrderedMCSs

public MCSData[] getOrderedMCSs(ConstraintNetwork peak)
Get a list of MCSData objects, ordered according to decreasing k, where k is a heuristic estimator of the amount of flexibility which is maintained when imposing a temporal constraint that resolves an MCS - see [P. Laborie, M. Ghallab, "Planning with Sharable Resource Constraints", IJCAI 1995].

Parameters:
peak - The peaks from which to sample MCSs and compute the k-based ordering.
Returns:
An ordered array of MCSData objects.
